---
import ClaimsTable from '../ClaimsTable.astro';
const rows = [
  { claim: 'Mn₃Sn supports deterministic 40-ps switching at 1.7 pJ/µm² energy density', tag: 'DEMONSTRATED' as const, source: 'Tsai et al., Science 2026' },
  { claim: 'Hopfion annihilation barrier exceeds 50 k_B T in EuS/Bi₂Se₃/EuS at 300 K, zero field', tag: 'DEMONSTRATED' as const, source: 'Katmis et al., Adv. Mater. 2025' },
  { claim: 'DISH enables sub-second (0.6 s) 3D scaffolding with 19 µm resolution on fixed surfaces', tag: 'DEMONSTRATED' as const, source: 'Wang et al., Nature 2026' },
  { claim: 'Landauer\'s erasure bound is the Delete-specific limit of a broader CRUD information-thermodynamic framework', tag: 'DEMONSTRATED' as const, source: 'Iizumi, Physica A 2026' },
  { claim: 'Planar-first, electrically read, multilayer spintronic stack is the minimum credible path', tag: 'INFERRED' as const, source: 'Alternative Materials' },
  { claim: 'TOHE provides an unambiguous all-electrical hallmark for 3D hopfions', tag: 'INFERRED' as const, source: 'Göbel & Lounis 2025/2026' },
  { claim: 'Classical reversible logic can be proposed using coherent spin dynamics in semiconductor quantum-dot arrays', tag: 'INFERRED' as const, source: 'Loss, arXiv:2607.06219v1' },
  { claim: 'Quantum reservoir performance links to microscopic energetic cost via Holevo memory/predictive capacities', tag: 'INFERRED' as const, source: 'Ding & Qiu, arXiv:2607.02157v1' },
  { claim: 'Direct conformal deposition of Fe₃GaTe₂ on a 3D polymer scaffold is unverified', tag: 'PROPOSED' as const, source: 'Fabrication notes' },
  { claim: 'MCA: deterministic Compute-in-Memory via SOT-driven domain wall shifting', tag: 'PROPOSED' as const, source: 'Core Architecture' },
  { claim: 'BRC: noise-driven nonlinear reservoir using ambient heat as the locomotive force', tag: 'PROPOSED' as const, source: 'Core Architecture' },
  { claim: 'Zero-field or low-bias hopfion operation is a demonstrated capability in EuS/Bi₂Se₃/EuS', tag: 'INFERRED' as const, source: 'Katmis et al., Adv. Mater. 2025' },
  { claim: 'HELIOS-3D targets ultra-low energy computation near efficiency limits', tag: 'SPECULATIVE' as const, source: 'Project framing' },
  { claim: 'Y-zipper mechanism supports reconfigurable or deployable 3D scaffolds', tag: 'PROPOSED' as const, source: 'Li et al., CHI 2026' },
  { claim: 'TLPs ("Flying Doughnuts") enable robust inter-module topological data transfer', tag: 'PROPOSED' as const, source: 'Niu et al., 2026' },
  { claim: 'Operation-level thermodynamic accounting is achievable in BRC via geometric confinement', tag: 'SPECULATIVE' as const, source: 'BRC theory' },
];
---
<section class="my-12 space-y-6">
  <p class="text-parchment-2 text-lg max-w-3xl">
    Every claim in the matrix is mapped to one of four validation lanes to clarify what is empirically backed vs. speculative:
  </p>

  <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6 my-8">
    <!-- Lane 1: Literature Evidence -->
    <div class="glass-card p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/20 bg-green-500/5 hover:border-green-500/35 transition-all">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-green-400"></span>
        <h4 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-green-400 font-bold">1. Literature Evidence</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-parchment/90 mb-2 font-semibold">Verified Empirical Studies</p>
      <ul class="text-[11px] text-parchment-2/80 space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Room-temp zero-field hopfions (Katmis 2025)</li>
        <li>40-ps SAF SOT switching (Tsai 2026)</li>
        <li>DISH 3D printing in 0.6s (Wang 2026)</li>
        <li>CRUD information thermodynamics (Iizumi 2026)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Lane 2: Simulation Validation -->
    <div class="glass-card p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/20 bg-blue-500/5 hover:border-blue-500/35 transition-all">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-blue-400"></span>
        <h4 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-blue-400 font-bold">2. Simulation</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-parchment/90 mb-2 font-semibold">Executable Validation Models</p>
      <ul class="text-[11px] text-parchment-2/80 space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>SAF DMI magnetic stack modeling (MuMax3)</li>
        <li>SOT nucleation field thresholds (OOMMF)</li>
        <li>Stochastic skyrmion MNIST baseline (Python)</li>
        <li>Ensemble noise averaging models</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Lane 3: Compiler Abstraction -->
    <div class="glass-card p-5 rounded-xl border border-orange-500/20 bg-orange-500/5 hover:border-orange-500/35 transition-all">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-orange-400"></span>
        <h4 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-orange-400 font-bold">3. Compiler Abstraction</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-parchment/90 mb-2 font-semibold">Synthesized Code & Logic</p>
      <ul class="text-[11px] text-parchment-2/80 space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Semantic vector -> 3D magnet tensor mapping</li>
        <li>Spin Conformation Language (Spin-ConfSeq)</li>
        <li>Boundary-constrained LLG (NeuroDiffEq)</li>
        <li>DISH optical inverse design loop (PINNs)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Lane 4: Hardware Speculation -->
    <div class="glass-card p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/20 bg-purple-500/5 hover:border-purple-500/35 transition-all">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-purple-400"></span>
        <h4 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-purple-400 font-bold">4. Speculative Target</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-parchment/90 mb-2 font-semibold">Long-Range Hardware Spec</p>
      <ul class="text-[11px] text-parchment-2/80 space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Conformal Fe₃GaTe₂ on TPP 3D scaffolds</li>
        <li>Sub-ns optical hopfion write (IFE periscope)</li>
        <li>Zero-bias BRC cores powered by ambient heat</li>
        <li>TOHE electrical readout & breathing network</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-parchment-2 text-sm max-w-3xl">
    Filter by claim stage using the chips below. Every claim is registered in <code class="text-amber font-mono">src/content/docs/current/claims-matrix.mdx</code> with a citation and a promotion/demotion criterion.
  </p>
  <ClaimsTable rows={rows} />
</section>
